00:34:10,810 --> 00:34:14,290
You have arrived at your destination.

560
00:34:48,690 --> 00:34:50,580
Help!

561
00:34:50,590 --> 00:34:53,630
Please! Somebody!

562
00:35:13,090 --> 00:35:15,720
I can't believe I let you drag me
to that movie in the first place.

563
00:35:15,730 --> 00:35:19,890
Not only was it moronic, it
was long. Look at the time.

564
00:35:20,380 --> 00:35:23,370
I'm sorry you didn't like the film,dear.

565
00:35:23,710 --> 00:35:26,550
What on earth? Not a second one.

566
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:29,320
This way you know how
far over you can be.

567
00:35:29,330 --> 00:35:33,570
As if I don't know how to park
my own car in my own garage.

568
00:35:33,580 --> 00:35:35,770
When did you put this
nonsense up anyway?

569
00:35:35,790 --> 00:35:38,190
This afternoon.

570
00:35:38,200 --> 00:35:41,980
That's why you parked my car in the
driveway and let the sprinklers get it wet.

571
00:35:41,990 --> 00:35:44,670
Oh,for goodness' sakes...

572
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:47,100
Wait. I haven't shown
you the best part yet.

573
00:35:47,110 --> 00:35:49,260
What,Tim? What is the best part?

574
00:35:49,270 --> 00:35:53,350
Look. Over there.

575
00:35:53,700 --> 00:35:55,820
I-I-I don't
see anything.

576
00:35:55,830 --> 00:35:59,520
Inside the vise. Do you see?

577
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:03,610
What is that? It
almost looks like a gun.

578
00:36:03,620 --> 00:36:06,900
It is. It is a gun.

579
00:36:06,910 --> 00:36:09,050
What on earth is that doing there?

580
00:36:09,060 --> 00:36:10,450
Watch.

581
00:36:54,730 --> 00:36:56,490
Hey,thanks for giving me a ride,Lee.

582
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:58,330
I didn't know who else to call.

583
00:36:58,340 --> 00:37:00,470
Joe doesn't have a car today.

584
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,770
It's fine,Allison.

585
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:07,960
I'm still trying to make sense
out of everything you just told me.

586
00:37:07,970 --> 00:37:10,480
You and me both.

587
00:37:10,490 --> 00:37:11,740
So let's say that is what happened.

588
00:37:11,750 --> 00:37:15,170
Let's say he did kill
her. How do we prove it?

589
00:37:15,180 --> 00:37:18,770
I-I don't know. Get a
search warrant, find the gun.

590
00:37:18,780 --> 00:37:22,230
No judge is going to give me a warrant
on the basis of a dream or a hallucination

591
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:24,390
or whatever it was you had back there.

592
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:27,870
Frankly,I'd be amazed
if he still had the gun.

593
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:32,610
Might be some blowback on the vise we could tie
to whatever they recover from the car,but still.

594
00:37:32,940 --> 00:37:37,150
I'll never get a warrant to take a
forensics team in there and find out.

595
00:37:38,380 --> 00:37:41,730
Boy,I'd love to talk to him again;
love to take a look around that garage.

596
00:37:41,740 --> 00:37:43,150
Well,it's wide open.

597
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:46,050
The car's sitting right there.
The keys are in the ignition...

598
00:37:46,060 --> 00:37:49,040
if the garage hasn't
closed itself already.

599
00:37:49,050 --> 00:37:52,550
That's certainly going to freak
him out when he gets back from work.

600
00:37:52,970 --> 00:37:56,100
I'd expect some angry
phone calls tonight.

601
00:37:56,960 --> 00:37:59,140
I guess he heard you.

602
00:38:01,350 --> 00:38:02,440
Hello?

603
00:38:02,450 --> 00:38:04,330
Allison,what the hell's going on?

604
00:38:04,340 --> 00:38:06,110
What do you mean? What
are you talking about?

605
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:09,740
The guy I told you about came by
the house to see the car today.

606
00:38:09,750 --> 00:38:12,620
He couldn't find anything.
He couldn't find you.

607
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:16,020
Oh,my God. I'm so sorry,Joe.

608
00:38:16,030 --> 00:38:20,180
I don't even know... how to begin.

609
00:38:20,190 --> 00:38:23,530
Well,it doesn't matter
now. He's never coming back.

610
00:38:24,340 --> 00:38:27,540
Hey,when you coming home?
When can I come pick you up?

611
00:38:27,550 --> 00:38:30,180
When the time comes, I'll
probably just take a cab.

612
00:38:30,190 --> 00:38:32,680
It might not be until really late.

613
00:38:32,690 --> 00:38:35,760
We got word the patent
guys might call tonight.

614
00:38:35,770 --> 00:38:39,910
She's got a,um, she's
got a date and I'm...

615
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:43,340
since I'm the minority partner, I've
got to sit and baby-sit the phones.

616
00:38:43,390 --> 00:38:46,070
I don't get it. Why do they have
to call in the middle of the night?

617
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:47,900
Why can't they call your cell?

618
00:38:47,910 --> 00:38:51,110
Allison,I don't know. It's Eastern
Europe. There's a time difference.

619
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:54,390
I don't know why she didn't
give them my cell,but she didn't.

620
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:56,250
Look,I've got to go now.

621
00:38:56,270 --> 00:38:58,240
I'm sorry about the car.

622
00:38:58,250 --> 00:39:01,000
Oh,we'll figure it out.

623
00:39:05,950 --> 00:39:08,430
Thanks for the ride,Lee.
Thanks for everything.

624
00:39:08,440 --> 00:39:10,620
Hey,you know what?

625
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:15,820
You need someone to pick up the SUV
from Carmer,right? It's still yours.

626
00:39:16,710 --> 00:39:20,380
Maybe I'll drop by Carmer's tonight,
drive over there with another officer.

627
00:39:20,390 --> 00:39:21,590
Say we're there to pick up the car.

628
00:39:21,610 --> 00:39:24,170
Use it as an excuse to
go through the garage.

629
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:26,670
You get your car back.
Maybe I get some evidence.

630
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:29,630
Oh,my God, that would be amazing.

631
00:39:31,140 --> 00:39:32,550
Power.

632
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:36,720
It takes many forms,
revealing itself in many ways.

633
00:39:36,730 --> 00:39:40,660
"At the bottom of a hill
lived Jack and his mother.

634
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:46,160
"And by the side of their little cottage,
Jack had planted a very large bean."

635
00:39:46,170 --> 00:39:48,440
Is this Jack and the Beanstalk?

636
00:39:48,450 --> 00:39:51,300
That's a boy story,Mom.
You can't read a boy story.

637
00:39:51,310 --> 00:39:55,230
- Dad's got to read that.
- Yeah,that's a boy story.

638
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:57,450
The idea that a waterfall
a thousand miles away

639
00:39:57,460 --> 00:40:02,110
makes it possible for me to
turn on a lamp seems like magic.

640
00:40:02,530 --> 00:40:05,140
That I can fill a bathtub with hot
water in the middle of the night

641
00:40:05,150 --> 00:40:08,130
makes no logical sense,either.

642
00:40:08,530 --> 00:40:11,410
Electricity,serendipity...

643
00:40:11,420 --> 00:40:17,500
they both surround us, both doing
their work silently, invisibly.

644
00:40:21,380 --> 00:40:23,180
Lee?

645
00:40:23,450 --> 00:40:25,430
You hear something?

646
00:40:35,510 --> 00:40:36,670
Hello?

647
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:38,920
You love me?

648
00:40:38,930 --> 00:40:41,490
Of course I love you.

649
00:40:42,260 --> 00:40:45,000
Did you get your call?
Are you coming home?

650
00:40:45,010 --> 00:40:47,160
No,no,and yes.

651
00:40:47,170 --> 00:40:50,340
I got another call. I
found a buyer for the SUV.

652
00:40:50,350 --> 00:40:51,740
You're kidding?

653
00:40:51,750 --> 00:40:57,800
it turns out that mechanic is serious about
how much he loves Carmer's death-mobile.

654
00:40:57,810 --> 00:40:59,290
He wants to buy it.

655
00:40:59,300 --> 00:41:02,550
And he's willing to pay us
$500 more than we paid Carmer,

656
00:41:02,570 --> 00:41:04,730
which is a good thing because
I think we're going to need it.

657
00:41:04,740 --> 00:41:06,850
What do you mean? What for?

658
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:12,310
He thinks I'm nuts and I think I'm nuts, but
I told him to go ahead and fix your old car.

659
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:16,980
Joe,that is so exciting!
That is fantastic!

660
00:41:16,990 --> 00:41:20,260
Honey,hold on a second.
I'm getting another call.

661
00:41:20,430 --> 00:41:21,860
Hello?

662
00:41:21,870 --> 00:41:24,030
Allison,it's Lee. You sitting down?

663
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:26,160
Well,kind of.

664
00:41:26,190 --> 00:41:28,530
He's dead,Allison.

665
00:41:28,540 --> 00:41:30,200
What are you talking about?

666
00:41:30,220 --> 00:41:34,090
Tim Carmer,he died from
carbon monoxide poisoning.

667
00:41:34,100 --> 00:41:38,510
When we got here,we noticed the garage
door was down, locked up tight as a drum.

668
00:41:38,530 --> 00:41:41,460
You could hear the SUV running in there.

669
00:41:41,470 --> 00:41:44,110
Oh,my God.

670
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:49,090
I just kept thinking about that story you
told me this afternoon, and wondering...

671
00:41:49,100 --> 00:41:52,020
was this something he did to himself?

672
00:41:52,030 --> 00:41:57,520
Or you think maybe
he,uh... It's crazy,right?

673
00:42:02,850 --> 00:42:05,690
Hey,Al,you still there?

674
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:13,870
It's okay. I think...
I think I lost her.

675
00:42:14,260 --> 00:42:17,370
I thought you were
out with the boyfriend.

676
00:42:17,380 --> 00:42:19,600
Best-laid plans...

677
00:42:19,630 --> 00:42:22,370
Or not laid,as the case may be.

